cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with visual recognition and classification tasks using recurrent neural networks and attention mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves large-scale pre-training and end-to-end training of neural networks, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The use of recurrent neural networks and attention mechanisms also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as word embeddings, which could also make cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category.
